%python df_anzsco = pd.read_pickle('/data/pickles/anzsco_small.pkl') df_timeseries = pd.read_pickle('/data/pickles/anzsco_timeseries_salary_with_5y_predictions.pkl') anzsco_codes = df_anzsco['ANZSCO'].unique() states = df_anzsco['State'].unique() state_names= ['Australian Capital Territory', 'New South Wales', 'Victoria', 'Queensland', "Tasmania",'South Australia', 'Northern Territory', 'Western Australia'] state_abbr= ['ACT', 'NSW', 'VIC', 'QLD', 'TAS', 'SA', 'NT', 'WA'] state_dict = {x:state_names[i] for i,x in enumerate(state_abbr)} anzsco_dict_vals = df_anzsco[['ANZSCO', 'ANZSCO Name']].sort_values(by='ANZSCO Name').drop_duplicates().values anzsco_dict = {x[0]: x[1] for x in anzsco_dict_vals} user_anzsco_code = z.select("Occupation (ANZSCO Unit Group)", anzsco_dict_vals) user_state = z.select("State", list(zip(state_abbr, state_names)) ) user_anzsco_name = anzsco_dict[str(user_anzsco_code)] user_state_name = state_dict[user_state] user_anzsco_minorgroup = user_anzsco_code[:3] print('%html

{} in {}

'.format(user_anzsco_name, user_state_name)) print('%html Here is information about the average salary for your occupation in your state compares against the national average. Also show are the predicted changes to the job market in your field, with respect to number of available jobs and salary.') df_user = df_anzsco[(df_anzsco['ANZSCO']==user_anzsco_code) & (df_anzsco['State']==user_state)][df_anzsco.columns[4:]] df_user_state = df_user[['Average Salary ($) (State)', 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) (State)','Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years (State)']] df_user_national = df_user[['Average Salary ($) (National)', 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) (National)','Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years (National)']] df_user_summary = pd.DataFrame(data = np.concatenate([df_user_state.values,df_user_national.values]).T, columns = ['State','National'], index=['%html

{}

'.format(x) for x in ['Average Salary ($)', 'Predicted Wage Growth Over Next 5 Years ($)', 'Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years']]) df_user_summary = df_user_summary.reset_index() df_user_summary.columns = [' ', user_state_name,'National'] z.show(df_user_summary) years = list(df_timeseries.index) # year_given = list(range(2011, 2018)) # years_[red ] plt.plot(years,df_timeseries[user_anzsco_code], '-o') plt.grid() plt.xlabel('Year', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold') plt.ylabel('Salary ($)', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold') plt.title('Predicted Salary Changes for {}'.format(user_anzsco_name+'\n in '+user_state_name), fontsize=16, fontweight='bold') print('%html

Looking for similar jobs in your field?

') print('%html Are you looking to make a career change? You can sort by any of the columns. For example, you might be interested in looking at careers which have many new job openings in the future; or you might be interested in career paths that offer high wage growth.') user_anzsco_minorgroup df_tmp = df_anzsco[(df_anzsco['ANZSCO Minor Group']==user_anzsco_minorgroup) & (df_anzsco['State']==user_state)][[ 'ANZSCO', 'ANZSCO Name', 'Average Salary ($) (State)', 'Average Salary ($) (National)', 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) (State)', 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) (National)', 'Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years (State)', 'Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years (National)'] ] df_tmp.columns = ['ANZSCO', 'ANZSCO Name', 'Average Salary ($) ({})'.format(user_state_name), 'Average Salary ($) (National)', 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) ({})'.format(user_state_name), 'Predicted 5-Year Wage Growth ($) (National)', 'Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years ({})'.format(user_state_name), 'Predicted New Jobs Over Next 5 Years (National)'] df_tmp.values[:,2:] = df_tmp.values[:,2:].astype(np.float) # This is needed because sometimes Zeppelin wants to interpret the entire table as strings z.show(df_tmp) print('%html

Innovation precincts in your area

') print('%html Here is a list of innovation precincts that are near you. Collaborating with innovation precincts can be a great way to indentify new and exciting work opportunities.') df_precinct = pd.read_pickle('/data/pickles/precincts.pkl') z.show(df_precinct[df_precinct['State']==user_state][['University', 'Centre/Precinct', 'Investment & main partners', 'Focus sectors', 'Interesting facts']])

paragraphs.text:
%python

anzsco_codes = list(df_tmp['ANZSCO'].values)
df_timeseries_codes = df_timeseries.columns
common_codes = list(set(anzsco_codes).intersection(set(df_timeseries_codes)))

df_timeseries_tmp = df_timeseries[common_codes].transpose().copy()
df_timeseries_tmp = df_timeseries_tmp.dropna(0)

if len(common_codes)>0:
    years = list(df_timeseries.index)
    new_df = pd.DataFrame(data =df_timeseries_tmp.values.astype(np.double).T, columns=common_codes, index=years )
    z.show(new_df)
